NOPE, The theft deductible is 1% of the value of your home. So if you have a $200,000 home, the 1st $2000 comes out of your pocket, so I got nothing back for my loss. title: For Sale:  DOLOS Rapid Barrel Removapl       ####LAST ONE####
postcontent: The Dolos theory of operation is incredibly simple. The barrel nut is separated into two parts. A tri-lug is attached to a standard AR15 upper receiver. A lock collar captures the barrel and gas tube, and is attached to a free float handguard. To employ the system, carefully insert the gas tube and barrel into the upper receiver and twist the lock collar up to 1/3 of a turn. You will hear and feel the ratchet lock as the lock collar seats into the tri-lug. Your barrel is now securely attached and your rifle ready for battle. Any standard front gas block can be used with the Dolos, from an A pillar sight post to a low profile or railed gas block. Simply purchase a free float tube for your particular gas system. Why do I need Dolos? •Real firepower right here, right now. title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom made 7 mm Remeington
postcontent: Custom made 7 mm Remington Magnum Rifle in good condition with Weaver 2.5 to 7 power scope. Action was made in Belgium and the 26” barrel has a muzzle break. It was embedded in a nice walnut stock by CD miller. Has recoil pad built in. Comes with padded leather tooled case and loaded ammo and empty brass. The rifling in the barrel has a bit to slow of a twist (1-11) so it will not stabilize bullets heavier than 160 grain bullets, but there is no need for those unless you go to Africa to hunt.  I suggest that ammo for this gun be hand loaded to the listed safe max, which I have done. I shot two rounds of 160 grain bullets in a 9/16 group and three bullets into a 1 ¼” group at 150 yards. It is a very powerful cartridge. All my kills on deer and a very large elk have been one shot instant kills. In fact, this cartridge is too powerful for deer unless you plan on long range shots over 200 yards. It is excellent for elk. I have had this rifle since late 60. I hunted for about 15 years then quit about 25 years ago due to my age. Most all my successful hunts had me firing one shot per year.
